title: Virtual Rally to Save the Cornerstone of Conservation Science
description:
We need YOU as we rally in support of critical federal government services at risk of being lost forever. The U.S. Geological Survey Ecosystems Mission Area is responsible for many of the programs that serve millions of birders, hunters, anglers, gardeners, biologists, ecologists, and wildlife enthusiasts around the country–and importantly, the wildlife we treasure. This mission area is set to be completely eliminated in less than two weeks. 

Without it, we will lose the backbone of environmental and ecological monitoring in the United States. This includes research that enables states to set hunting seasons, allows conservationists to understand and respond to declines in birds, bees and other wildlife, and tracks dangerous wildlife diseases and environmental pollutants that impact people and biodiversity. 

Join us and our incredible lineup of speakers, including **renowned conservation leaders and authors Dr. J. Drew Lanham and Kenn Kaufman,** to learn about the critical work of the USGS, show off your best poster featuring your favorite wildlife species, and take action to urge your elected officials to save the Ecosystems Mission Area. Together, we will stand up for the public services that protect our communities, our wildlife, and our future!

*This event is co-sponsored by American Fisheries Society, Ecological Society of America, Xerces Society for Invertebrate Conservation, Society for Conservation Biology North America, The Wildlife Society, Entomological Society of America, American Bird Conservancy, Atlanta Botanical Garden, and America the Beautiful for All Coalition.*

title: Protest 287(g) in PWC
description:
May 21st 2025
4:45pm-7:30pm
Adult Detention Center - 9320 Lee Ave, Manassas

In response to the Manassas GOP’s call to reinstate the 287(g) program at the Prince William-Manassas Regional Jail, local Democratic leaders, immigrant rights advocates, and concerned residents will gather peacefully outside the Jail Board meeting on Wednesday, May 21, 2025 at 6pm, to reject policies rooted in racial profiling, fear-mongering, and the criminalization of immigrant communities.

We stand for a Prince William County and City of Manassas that welcomes all residents, regardless of immigration status. The 287(g) program has historically eroded trust between law enforcement and immigrant families, making communities less safe and more divided.

The PWCDC Latino Caucus and community advocates firmly opposes any efforts to revive the 287(g) agreement, which was discontinued in 2020 due to widespread concerns about civil rights violations, discriminatory enforcement, and costly legal challenges. Reinstating it would represent a dangerous step backward and undermine the values of inclusion and due process.

Attendees of the counter-protest are encouraged to bring signs, wear green as a symbol of unity, and submit public comments demanding humane, community-centered approaches to public safety.

We will not be silent while extremist agendas threaten the dignity and safety of our neighbors. We call on all people of conscience to stand with us in solidarity.
